Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> we also happen to hide all communications in the metadata of a financial transaction! Devious! ðŸ™‚

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> This is very important and why XMR-based memo competitors, are severely not as private

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> When you use the `extra` field in XMR, the whole world knows how much data you put in, they can see, and they know which xtns use it and which don't

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> In Zcash Protocol, every single xtn has 512 bytes of encrypted memo, no matter what. If you use it or not. So nobody can tell which xtns are financial and which are communications!

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> This is critical, and for instance, LOKI does not have that

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> LOKI uses masternodes to pass around your specially encrypted message, and that stands out like crazy

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> And not to poke fun of LOKI, this is in the deep XMR protocol. All cryptonote-based coins have this problem
